oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Grand Ole Opry - Prince Albert - 1960-11-19 - Part 1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Part 1 of Prince Albert tobacco sponsored Grand Ole Opry segment from November 19, 1960. Featuring Grant Turner (announcer), the Wilburn Brothers (hosts/performers), guest performer Bobby Helms, and regular performers Archie Campbell, Tommy Jackson, Chet Atkins, Minnie Pearl, the Jordanaires, and Grandpa Jones. Held at Ryman Auditorium, Nashville, TN. It is announced that this is the 1102nd broadcast.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Wilburn Brothers; Archie Campbell; Bobby Helms; Tommy Jackson; Chet Atkins
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Grant Turner introduces the Wilburn Brothers -- Someone Else's Love (Wilburn Brothers) -- Opening statement (Grant Turner) and special guest Bobby Helms -- Doyle Wilburn introduces Archie Campbell -- Comedy routine (Archie Campbell, Wilburn Brothers) -- Doyle Wilburn introduces Bobby Helms -- Fraulein (Bobby Helms) -- Prince Albert commercial (Grant Turner, Wilburn Brothers) -- Doyle Wilburn introduces Tommy Jackson -- Leather Britches (Tommy Jackson fiddle) -- Grant Turner and the Wilburn Brothers talk -- I'll Never Leave My God Alone (Wilburn Brothers) -- Grant Turner introduces Chet Atkins -- Tiger Rag (Chet Atkins)
